skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "022d2c61-3221-4c5f-a163-1127684483b4", "value": "A ship that is built and primarily intended for war."}

{"id": "785174c3-cf8d-40da-9d41-e346b08a6cb4", "value": "A freelance boat used off the south and east coasts of England to provide passing ships with pilots, supplies, new anchors and other gear. Some helped sailing ships and barges get underway. Generally lug-rigged. Also used for fishing. Half decked."}
{"id": "361520f0-b8e0-43ec-b1de-0c1a0fc1d55c", "value": "Craft intended for recreation and not intended for any commercial use."}
{"id": "e705f730-8e7e-4fb7-8678-726090c9be8e", "value": "A steam vessel propelled by rotating propellers called screws."}
{"id": "4bcbd2b3-0157-402f-b115-519cf587bbd7", "value": "A relatively small and heavily built vessel equipped with large engines. Used for towing ships at sea or manouevring them in tight spaces."}
{"id": "9c6fe4a2-2a05-4d30-ac48-80dff1607031", "value": "An old ship converted for a variety of uses for which it is not required to move under its own power."}
{"id": "65972ba1-ee55-4d7d-b3d7-084082393095", "value": "The largest boat belonging to a sailing vessel, and usually the means of escape from a sinking ship; powered by oars."}
{"id": "102321ca-a1db-4b11-ba1e-4b9c10a9b5d3", "value": "A steam vessel propelled by a pair of paddle wheels amidships or a single wheel astern, driven by a reciprocating engine."}

{"id": "0d94dbc4-6b9f-4712-a620-97e02bf2d28b", "value": "Generic name for a vessel used for work rather than for recreation, transportation, or military purposes. The vessels include tugs, barges, landing craft, dredgers and standby safety vessels. Use only were the exact type of vessel is unknown."}
{"id": "f1550fac-7b46-41a4-8bd3-f12874bba248", "value": "Generic name for a small steam or power boat often carried on board a larger vessel."}
{"id": "6e5c91e8-78e0-4594-a14d-651c7e755fe2", "value": "All vessels, use more specific type where known."}
{"id": "db331646-21f2-47a8-8883-520ca27b1205", "value": "Vehicle either adapted, or purpose-built, to operate on both land and sea, for example a tank or DUKW."}
{"id": "830468bb-9bb9-4771-8c80-a5bd80346a73", "value": "A vessel fitted with a catapult for launching an aircraft."}
{"id": "27834521-4019-4b1b-9bc0-0e494669843b", "value": "A vessel equipped with sealed tanks for transporting sewage and dumping it in deep water."}
{"id": "46f3ad64-b470-4645-b184-f198424b839e", "value": "A sailing vessel defined by a combination of such factors as hull design, locality and rig."}
{"id": "7a6c1304-b5a2-4fe3-9d4e-e726d398f485", "value": "A ship used for laying cables (often telephone cables) along the sea bed."}

{"id": "70e0eee5-0436-4b1a-8f6f-cbc0dce387fc", "value": "Any boat used to transfer crew from shore to an offlying vessel. May also carry the catch from a fishing boat to shore. Used as special boats by the Royal National Lifeboat Institution for conveying crew from the beach to a moored lifeboat."}
{"id": "8fc2c2e1-0c1a-4aec-9a3a-33989b23abce", "value": "A private fighting ship under a letter of marque or financed by subscribers, shareholders or individuals."}
{"id": "5aac4840-cc56-4c9c-a22e-a8aa9e7cd539", "value": "Vessels of various types used specifically for providing an initial training in seamanship."}

{"id": "9e606335-0b86-4bd0-a1bb-a5c51bc5ff5c", "value": "A hulk or obsolete vessel filled with cement or similar material and scuttled to block an entrance to a port or anchorage, usually as a defensive measure."}
{"id": "1a2bc04a-925f-405f-8848-b773b34d6aec", "value": "A craft built with the intention of demonstrating or advertising a novel design feature."}
{"id": "35e7bc25-e0c2-4f9f-ad68-f6f932c8fdec", "value": "A large ship's boat powered by oars and or an engine."}

{"id": "3481c7b3-d8d3-44cb-9585-2715f445dd0b", "value": "A vessel used to carry essential supplies, such as food and armaments, to naval ships in order to keep them replenished whilst on patrol. Use more specific term."}
{"id": "b0db6305-cf18-4d48-a9fd-526922ecfca2", "value": "A flat floating framework of planks or other materials used for supporting or carrying persons or goods."}

{"id": "2a1dc60e-36ce-4c8c-a826-bba2a24f41bd", "value": "Cargo vessel or warship captured by a warship or privateer of a hostile nation in time of war, usually taken into that nation\ufffds mercantile, privateering or naval service."}
{"id": "88c0c226-c320-475e-84f6-9c1b2cee7d31", "value": "A buoy with a compartment into which shipwrecked mariners could climb to await rescue."}
{"id": "3361932f-3af7-4ff4-9437-abee86baf69e", "value": "The characteristics of a sailing vessel where her type is determined by her masts and sails."}
{"id": "05911231-c3d2-4329-91cb-488009152201", "value": "A vessel or craft used for catching or harvesting marine life by a variety of methods, use specific method where known."}

{"id": "54bd1cd5-1cfc-431a-a8a9-838a442083c9", "value": "A barge with a lugsail rig commonly found on the River Thames in the late 19th century. Also a general term applied to the family of Deal luggers."}

{"id": "cccb08dd-b6bb-4359-b8f2-cf4a7b0e09bd", "value": "Any vessel in the service of one of the historical or modern agencies concerned with the prevention of inbound or outbound smuggling: namely the Preventive Service, the Coastguard, or the Customs and Excise. Use more specific term."}
{"id": "33fd136c-7747-42aa-957d-4efb6fba6f99", "value": "A vessel used to maintain supply or assist larger vessels. Use more specific term."}

{"id": "757cdcd3-09b8-42aa-b353-22b4a890b33c", "value": "Small, light, fast, all-purpose craft designed primarily for inland use. Generally flat-bottomed, often with rocker; sharp bow, sharp or transom stern, lapstrake or carvel planking. Propelled by oars, sails or motor. Used for fishing and leisure."}
{"id": "b388bc4a-6e8c-4775-b596-a02e36552a0f", "value": "Any vessel operated by Trinity house masters and brethren in the maintenance of lighthouses, lightships, buoys and other navigation aids."}
{"id": "60ab4829-76da-4e8d-955f-fceb2a00d5ad", "value": "A vessel with equipment for processing dead marine life whilst still at sea."}
{"id": "845df526-949e-4038-9520-d17d7301fa73", "value": "Oared fighting ship with ancillary sails."}
{"id": "d40d4b9c-7f93-45f2-970a-6f34435e2cff", "value": "A vessel, purpose-built or requisitioned, used for patrolling inland or coastal waters, e.g. Coastguard and Customs vessels."}
{"id": "ab503170-a10b-4d62-802b-b87e1d572534", "value": "A craft used to deepen shipping channels, harbours and other water courses."}
{"id": "8cf5bcb3-39a5-4e1d-be1e-7b68414b8322", "value": "Vessel fitted with broadcasting equipment and used for off-shore radio programme transmission."}
{"id": "d6479c2f-49c0-4c38-964d-179f79165339", "value": "A flat bottomed boat or hollow float of which a number are used to support a temporary bridge over a river."}
{"id": "612a4d7d-48a0-4e16-ba24-234360ab0392", "value": "The class term, use more specific terms."}
{"id": "fbe51c7c-ea5d-480d-8c3a-57685fcbda79", "value": "A boat used as private or domestic living accomodation."}

skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:description: {"id": "8ee6ad0d-98ad-417d-8a0c-77729c3de730", "value": "Used for recording types of watercraft which survive as wrecks or museums in Historic England's maritime record."}
skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:title: {"id": "a09e347e-8b82-46ab-a634-1d61db3898ff", "value": "FISH Maritime Craft Types"}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "22dead01-3606-481b-9303-87c8143d02d6", "value": "A craft which is equipped for and performs hydrographic surveys."}

{"id": "f9b1dcc5-5a1e-4776-8747-aa88725f7d44", "value": "An artificial harbour, constructed using prefabricated, concrete caissons, floating breakwaters and blockships, which were towed across the channel and assembled off the coast of Normandy to assist the allied forces after the D-Day landings in June 1944."}
{"id": "63bbce55-3592-4f20-90b1-4577d6939021", "value": "A vessel used for transporting passengers or goods."}
{"id": "601931b8-1334-49b9-a506-2ec116908f39", "value": "Large warship with no armour and a high speed. Used for reconnaisance and raids on enemy merchant shipping."}

{"id": "d44b671f-964a-4c6e-821d-67a0baaf3b02", "value": "Large warship equipped with turret mounted guns. Intended for independent action for trade protection, reconaissance and fire support for amphibious operations."}
{"id": "5fdc4854-df7b-4dd0-83fd-633779367e7e", "value": "Large inshore craft with a retractable loading ramp in the bow. Used to carry tanks ashore for a beach landing or as a tank ferry."}
{"id": "1846664a-563b-4144-b135-98d75d664149", "value": "A warship constructed of iron plate with its main armament mounted in a revolving turret on deck."}
{"id": "058d5c00-088b-4d92-a3de-8fd731bbe252", "value": "A cargo vessel constructed in the U.S.A. during World War II from prefabricated sections by welding."}

{"id": "8335bf4f-1820-451b-b402-51efff160946", "value": "A prefabricated cargo vessel produced in large numbers by North American shipyards during World War II to replace shipping losses caused by German submarines and replacing the earlier 'LIBERTY' ships."}
{"id": "2735c3f7-5612-4ec3-8297-67f5ba5a0cc0", "value": "A vessel, usually a merchant vessel, altered to resemble a warship or another vessel."}
{"id": "222dabf0-8859-46e5-b0d9-9e8c3f16e846", "value": "A civil vessel disguised as a warship."}
{"id": "d57bc854-82c3-428d-b4c3-cd7e1d2d64d0", "value": "A small merchant ship or warship with concealed weapons, intended as a trap for enemy submarines."}
{"id": "aaf291ab-052f-464d-8aa2-36d393a3e2f4", "value": "A warship used to provide an escort to other warships or merchant ships against attack."}
{"id": "412301da-2da6-4f43-a986-9029d17ebbcc", "value": "A three masted fully rigged warship armed with 24 to 38 guns on a single gundeck."}
{"id": "f718fbaf-8fe1-43ce-90f7-538d69569101", "value": "A medium speed anti submarine escort vessel built from World War II"}
{"id": "18c7c6f9-6138-4b6a-a287-dd29164e05d9", "value": "A flush decked sailing warship with a single tier of guns."}
{"id": "14089b35-12f7-4409-ab95-15ef0e68439d", "value": "A small warship (often adapted from a trawler or drifter) used to hunt enemy submarines."}
{"id": "24ac9c56-bb05-439e-8765-010091b3d9d4", "value": "A small anti submarine escort vessel built in World War II"}
{"id": "edd06711-4530-4eff-a34d-99d98f7ce03f", "value": "Small landing craft often armoured, designed to carry infantrymen and their equipment ashore from larger vessels offshore."}
{"id": "7db775d5-cbc5-492a-961f-21390852d81b", "value": "Dutch galliot-rigged vessel used mostly for river trade in Holland but sometimes also for coasting or short sea-going voyages"}
{"id": "fb9f8034-44c7-4a43-aa53-c211dae94824", "value": "A self propelled vessel for deepening harbours using a continuous chain of buckets"}
{"id": "a1f15fba-521c-4050-b45b-620cb55d45db", "value": "A small vessel used to attack other vessels and setting themselves and then the enemy alight."}
{"id": "eb0b1577-18bf-41e0-b54d-d94a65b4feaa", "value": "Flat bottomed vessel used as a platform for a pile driver."}
{"id": "878eb9d1-a7b6-41c6-bfed-2a159d8334ae", "value": "A vessel used to carry away mud etc from a dredging machine and discharging it elsewhere."}
{"id": "9a5253b3-2a44-4104-9aec-6945e01cde79", "value": "A shallow draft vessel used to carry a crane."}
{"id": "4347f6f0-aca6-4d11-a9f5-77b65694b7b5", "value": "A barge fitted with a large tank in its hull for carried liquid cargoes."}
{"id": "6cbba8dd-1e26-49bc-ba30-055376a65379", "value": "A barge with a crane or sheer legs used for moving and maintaining mooring buoys."}
{"id": "56588033-bf59-4988-a6d1-899d059f579e", "value": "A barge with a spritsail rig commonly found on the River Thames."}
{"id": "8aeb861a-6ebe-41f6-8cd7-fe9785d0e6f9", "value": "Shallow draft cargo vessel, often broad beamed and flat bottomed, powered by engine and or sail."}
{"id": "376d73fa-21e1-4946-866e-b161c479f9d9", "value": "Shallow draft vessel used to carry ammunition."}
{"id": "fea9adea-415d-4796-82c4-2bc300823957", "value": "A flat bottomed vessel for receiving mud and other material from a dredger."}
{"id": "16e7f40b-f5e9-48f3-8522-5ab7b8b824e0", "value": "Moored barge providing a refuge for shipwrecked sailors or downed airmen, for example the air-sea rescue Cuckoo barges of WWII."}
{"id": "d130e25e-26d7-44d7-a22a-99aab14ff269", "value": "A vessel carrying square sails on all masts and having three or more masts."}

{"id": "dc7afb45-e632-4fbd-b95d-724747365218", "value": "Dutch coaster of the late 17th to late 19th centuries with a square hull and 2 masts, generally having a heavy keel and round stern and bilges, although later examples were built on more refined lines."}

{"id": "3b9b97c9-16e5-4e8a-9dca-6122c328865a", "value": "A multihulled craft consisting of two hulls, or vakas, which are usually joined together by a frame or other structure, formed of akas. Catamarans can be sail or engine powered."}

{"id": "597473a4-118d-472e-a858-bd5d1933ed43", "value": "A term for any vessel powered principally by sail and oars, or oars alone, used especially for war. As a broad term it may refer to Roman galleys, or more specifically to an Anglo-Saxon or Norse warship of the Viking Age."}
{"id": "69c888f6-3b5a-4b9e-b745-92f2ca053a1a", "value": "A ship designed or modified to carry large numbers of mines and be able to lay them as a minefield."}
{"id": "142fff52-3f94-4086-bcfd-93418e301e01", "value": "Any vessel involved in the catching or transportation of whales."}
{"id": "cb167cd6-e114-4184-b7a5-6d89c98ed725", "value": "A craft employed to harpoon whales and bring them in to be processed."}
{"id": "0f283240-5234-4526-b8a4-7d5092c20e8f", "value": "Any vessel which has been hired or impressed for use by the Admiralty."}
{"id": "3510fe19-5486-4d0a-a6e5-989fb35d64ac", "value": "A small craft of wickerwork covered with waterproof material."}
{"id": "07049f98-7064-437a-a3d4-366920886f7a", "value": "A major warship equipped with a clear flat deck to provide a landing and taking off place for aircraft."}
{"id": "a2833e3d-f016-4e08-b274-1a314bf062f9", "value": "An air-cushioned vehicle capable of travelling over land or water."}
{"id": "bc651c02-8063-4f12-b702-2daa922adb5b", "value": "Small coastal vessel."}
{"id": "68f10c71-557d-440e-ae41-fd9c347f89da", "value": "Any vessel propelled by sail or power and used for pleasure and not plying for hire."}
{"id": "bbb787d4-f1dd-4994-ba6b-73e2a35cc7d4", "value": "A ship or brig peculiar to the Mediterranean."}
{"id": "9b47dfa6-6bcd-4e2d-b93f-169c7a42f63f", "value": "A small warship mounting between 20 and 28 nine-pounder guns on a single deck."}

{"id": "4a62984d-a158-46d8-ace6-549a7ebb835f", "value": "A boat specifically designed for saving lives at sea, they can be either: a boat carried on a larger vessel for use in emergency evacuation of crew and passengers in the event of shipwreck or a boat built for the purpose of shore-to-sea rescue missions."}

{"id": "7df350c5-1ef1-4dc2-bd24-f68965310460", "value": "A type of small boat that was often carried, or towed by a larger vessel and used as a ship's boat. Dinghies can also be used recreationally as independent sailing vessels."}
{"id": "6fc12c52-5997-467b-9072-f8572c143a1e", "value": "Small vessel built or adapted to lay and recover anti submarine nets in harbours and anchorages."}

{"id": "a86a0d2f-bf15-4bf9-a919-ea015653d39b", "value": "A vessel designed or adapted to sweep and explode mined areas at sea without prior detection. (See Minehunter for vessels that detect and destroy individual mines)."}

{"id": "b54c1524-ebe2-4038-9c85-657c7d03ae87", "value": "Originally denoting a Byzantine vessel, powered by oars, from the 6th century onwards, this developed into a large Mediterranean ship with oars and a single mast, used for trade or for war transport, (e.g. during the Crusades) until the 15th century."}
{"id": "00794639-897d-4710-8352-b109d7c05c43", "value": "A cargo vessel designed to carry goods packed in large containers that can be loaded directly onto trains or lorries."}
{"id": "253e9983-7800-4ca8-8247-3eab6fa83a7b", "value": "A single decked cargo vessel carrying the majority of its cargo on deck."}
{"id": "cd93787f-a806-4ec1-869e-4689b49d7110", "value": "A large cargo vessel, either purpose-fitted or converted, for the transportation of slaves."}
{"id": "3cfa9a93-bc45-434d-b5ef-503102d41f89", "value": "Large cargo vessel specially built and equipped for handling large quantities of ore."}

{"id": "4a3a3791-ca13-4ac5-8f03-a40eb3fd8b3e", "value": "Any one of the cargo vessels of that name belonging to the different Baltic nations, in use from the mid 18th to the early 20th century. Usually ketch-rigged. Not to be confused with the oared GALEASS."}
{"id": "1049018f-b70b-4667-865a-982061c481d6", "value": "A vessel designed principally for the carriage of fare paying passengers."}
{"id": "67f000ca-106c-4bc0-ab34-7ba3b1f17751", "value": "A vessel used for carrying cargoes, fitted with defensive weapons. Use with specific type and form where known."}
{"id": "c64513da-87bf-4224-8e47-ea045c6b70ad", "value": "A craft designed for use on canals and inland waterways. Usually 70ft long x 7ft wide though can be longer and broader."}

{"id": "dcbc29bf-b6dc-424b-9b59-d242a713e056", "value": "17th century Dutch vessel built for naval or East India service, with a relatively flat bottom and narrow hull; sometimes rendered into English as `fly-boat'."}
{"id": "549ff65f-07cd-4004-888d-92264c4c9097", "value": "A ship designed specifically for the carriage of liquid cargoes, particularly oil."}
{"id": "36e1bc26-b5fb-424a-91a4-99a4913c02ed", "value": "Small cargo vessel used for short coastal voyages carrying a variety of cargoes."}
{"id": "688a5116-822a-47b9-841d-84a1913934a9", "value": "A designed for the carriage of livestock usually cattle or sheep."}
{"id": "72559258-8ba0-49a0-97aa-db94cbc837f6", "value": "A vessel for carrying a cargo of coal in bulk."}
{"id": "f0beed77-7c48-4c67-a397-2e448d2b7c8f", "value": "A craft used for the transportation of cargoes. Use specific type where known."}
{"id": "38c6b6d5-0143-43d8-ac99-6a6219c4dd4e", "value": "A large Mediterranean cargo or transport vessel of the 15th to 17th century, usually less than 400 tons."}
{"id": "4c4c6567-e48f-433f-bf52-0d246081bdc0", "value": "Cargo vessel specially constructed to carry bulk items such as grain. Does not include liquid cargoes."}
{"id": "a29e283f-14ed-44e9-aa3f-3f77967d5e2f", "value": "A small cargo vessel used on the West coast of Scotland."}
{"id": "f173a436-1499-4a02-af0e-24f62026ee82", "value": "A ship of the line mounting between 90 and 98 guns on three gun decks"}
{"id": "47c5b0ba-2929-46a5-b003-e6a626e369c9", "value": "Two masted vessel with a square rig on both masts."}
{"id": "6bc7db5d-e482-4975-92f0-692ac44af23d", "value": "A vessel used to carry a pilot to a ship."}
{"id": "52140b85-6ff8-4dca-9dc0-bc7b154f8191", "value": "A ship used for treating patients or moving them between a battle zone and a safe area."}

{"id": "2cddfabf-6976-488a-a82b-ec835d271d0e", "value": "Transport vessel used for the repatriation of wounded troops, particularly during the First World War. Loosely described as \"hospital ships\", these ships were distinct from hospital ships proper by being defensively armed."}

{"id": "0310bd9d-2f22-43bb-849b-d31a7b73ba86", "value": "A fishing vessel which tows a dredger to gather oysters. This is an iron wedge shaped contrivance with a small net attached. Towed behind the vessel the iron wedge loosens the oysters and they fall into the net."}

{"id": "a8f2cbfb-c3db-4e2c-8569-d6847e5662d3", "value": "Small, heavily built coble, usually fitted with lugsail and oars, used on the north-east coast of England to assist, tow, pilot, provision or otherwise attend ships."}

{"id": "82c95eb5-ca98-4618-9dd3-81e1b0968c9a", "value": "A specially equipped ship designed to care for survivors of stricken vessels and offshore drilling platforms. These ships were often converted naval trawlers or minesweepers."}
{"id": "65433d5a-5355-424a-9130-a6dc1acf00b5", "value": "A rescue tug equipped to care for survivors from torpedoed vessels and also available for towing to port ships damaged by enemy action."}
{"id": "b0d45f56-4974-4af9-82f5-e3ee385d1e53", "value": "A three masted vessel with a square rig on the fore and main masts and lateen rig on the mizzen mast."}
{"id": "b65de1af-ce32-4045-a0a9-25fe06ded579", "value": "A sloop used for carrying weapons and ammunition to warships."}
{"id": "001f25f4-2d4e-4325-8f97-5f033840dabc", "value": "A vessel for maintaining the buoys, hawsers and netting of a boom defence."}
{"id": "ded61a4f-326f-40b9-8fc4-521fee15bfa1", "value": "A small, fast boat used for carrying orders between sailing vessels."}

{"id": "bc9843e3-91c9-4a12-aa65-55635de85a4a", "value": "A mine countermeasure vessel built to detect and destroy individual naval mines. (See Minesweeper for vessels that sweep and explode mined areas at sea without prior detection)."}

{"id": "bce5ead8-04e5-4390-afc5-f884aed1142e", "value": "A vessel designed or adapted for the task of keeping shipping lanes and ports free from the threat of naval mines. Use specific type where known. of"}
{"id": "573dae11-97f4-414a-81e7-8e3fa793e113", "value": "French warship broadly equivalent to the English 4th to 6th Rates, with as few as 4 to as many as 50 guns."}
{"id": "321ff042-15de-440e-ac5d-1ddcc428eecf", "value": "Large submarine intended to operate with a surface fleet at sea."}
{"id": "4673827a-a178-4da2-94ad-34f791788bf9", "value": "Diesel engined submarine designed for long ocean voyages in search of enemy shipping."}
{"id": "3bf9dc3b-7b96-428b-bbfe-90534fea3e90", "value": "British 'M' class submarine modified to carry and launch a small sea plane."}

{"id": "61968261-cca9-4f15-85d8-a30ccb174e5d", "value": "The British designation for any German submarine built for military purposes. U-Boat is an anglicization of the German U-Boot, an abbreviation for Unterseeboot (Undersea Boat). In German U-Boot refers to any submarine."}
{"id": "05338e0e-ff09-4b9c-a228-39ed77314543", "value": "A submarine built or adapted to carry mines and lay minefields."}
{"id": "5c2ff83c-efe7-4e7c-82e1-6184fc4eb1a2", "value": "A vessel designed to operate below the surface of the sea."}
{"id": "b313c075-129f-4dd2-b3b6-c13b16a566f0", "value": "Small submarine with a two or three man crew. Used for special missions such as sinking warships in heavily defended harbours."}
{"id": "b1f235aa-f8e0-45c0-8f4c-5bf303adaab0", "value": "First practical submarine design. The first to use a combination of battery power and internal combustion engines."}
{"id": "25f7f81e-40a1-4bf0-bdbf-becd13e512a1", "value": "Any vessel designed for speed or endurance racing."}
